En una reunión especial que ocurrió el jueves por la noche, 6 de agusto, la Junta Directiva aprobó la recomendación de comenzar la escuela en línea este otoño.Aunque fue una decisión difícil, dados los impactos inherentes en los estudiantes y las familias, creo que fue la decisión correcta. La recomendación se basó en el porcentaje de infecciones actualmente, el asesoramiento de la profesión médica, la colaboración con colegas regionales y el hecho de que la salud y la seguridad de nuestros estudiantes es la prioridad número uno de nuestro distrito escolar.

At a special meeting held on Thursday evening, August 6th, the Board of Directors approved the recommendation to start school online this fall. Although this was a difficult decision, given the inherent impacts on students and families, I believe this was the right decision. The recommendation was based on current infection rates, advice from the medical profession, collaboration with regional superintendent colleagues and the fact that the health and safety of our students is our number one priority.

Read the rest of the letter: https://core-docs.s3.amazonaws.com/documents/asset/uploaded_file/842885/LCSD_Re-Starting_School_Update_08.07.2020.pdf

Microsoft TEALS Program
August 6 at 9:00 AM ·

We are very excited to announce that Chelan High School and the 2019-20 TEALS teaching team are the recipients of the inaugural TEALS Founder's Award! Chelan has been committed to ensuring all students in the school have exposure to foundational computer science skills.

In celebration of the 10-year milestone of the TEALS Program, the TEALS Founder's Award was established in 2019. The award will be presented annually to a TEALS partner high school and teaching team that has gone above and beyond in building and growing a sustainable, diverse, and inclusive computer science program, as advocated by TEALS Program founder Kevin Wang.

post_text:
The Lake Chelan School District is preparing for school this fall, and are requesting that local residents and guests remove their boats and trailers from school parking lots.
-
Over the past few weeks, boat and trailer parking at the local high school has become problematic. Effective Sunday, August 2nd, no boats or trailers will be allowed to park in the main lot in front of the High School. All boats and trailers must be cleared so the space is available for school district use.
-
Boats and trailers will be allowed to park at the side and back parking lots until August 16th. Boats and trailers remaining on school parking lots after this date may be subject to towing.

Going back to school may not look exactly as we hoped but having school supplies and a backpack to keep them in is still important!

If your child needs school supplies and a backpack, load up in the car and drive up to Mountain Goat Field by Chelan Walmart on Sunday, August 9, from 4 - 6 pm to participate in the RealLife drive-thru backpack and supplies give away! Supplies are limited.

Thank you to the sponsors who helped make backpacks and supplies available for our communities.

post_text:
Chelan Athletics would like to announce the hiring of Tony Callero as our new Head Boys’ Basketball Coach at Chelan High School!

Tony played and graduated from Central Washington University. He has 14 years of high school coaching experience and 24 years of successful teaching. Tony has also coached collegiately at Seattle University as an assistant coach. Besides being a basketball coach and teacher at Auburn High School, Tony has run the Auburn Basketball Academy as well as co-founded the Auburn Select Basketball league.

We are very excited for Tony to join our athletic staff, as well as our teaching staff here at Chelan High/Middle School. He has great experience in coaching basketball, and we are super excited about his knowledge and experience in getting all ages of kids playing basketball throughout the year.

Tony will take on teaching duties for both Chelan High and Middle School starting this fall.

Tony played and graduated from Central Washington University. He has 14 years of high school coaching experience and 24 years of successful teaching. Tony has also coached collegiately at Seattle University as an assistant coach. Besides being a basketball coach and teacher at Auburn High School, Tony has run the Auburn Basketball Academy as well as co-founded the Auburn Select Basketball league.

We are very excited for Tony to join our athletic staff, as well as our teaching staff here at Chelan High/Middle School. He has great experience in coaching basketball, and we are super excited about his knowledge and experience in getting all ages of kids playing basketball throughout the year.

Tony will take on teaching duties for both Chelan High and Middle School starting this fall.

North Central Accountable Community Health (NCACH) announces the North Central Washington COVID-EO Contest, a project created to engage youth in Chelan, Douglas, Grant and Okanogan counties to learn about and bring awareness to the importance of CDC and local public health guidelines to reduce the rapid spread of the novel coronavirus in our four-county region.

The online contest from April 13 to May 15 is open to K-12 students who live in the four-county region and is located at www.woobox.com/9troqi.

shared_text:
Lake Chelan School District Food Service
March 31 at 10:55 AM ·

Hello everyone,

Beginning Monday, April 6th, the Chelan Middle/High school site will be closing.

We will be serving all drive through and walk up meals at the Morgen Owings Elementary site from 10:30-12:30.

Meal services will continue at Apple Acres and Chelan Falls from 10:30-11:30

There is a drop off point at the corner of Hwy 97 and Stayman Flats road for those who live in that general area. Meals can be picked up at that location between 10:45-11:00 am.

Thank you and stay safe!

post_text:
Beginning tomorrow (03/23/2020):
The meal service program for the Lake Chelan School District will support children 1-18 years of age in the Lake Chelan School District in the four pick up locations. We only ask that the children are present at the time of service.
1. Apple Acres Mobile Home Park 10:30am-11:30am.
2. Chelan Falls Park 10:30am-11:30am.
3. Morgen Owings Elementary 10:30am-12:30pm.
4. Chelan Middle/High School 10:30am-12:30pm.

El programa de alimentos del Distrito Escolar de Lake Chelan apoyará a todos los niños de 1-18 años de edad en el Distrito Escolar de Chelan en los cuatro lugares de recogida. Solo pedimos que los niños estén presentes al momento del servicio.

1. Parqueadero de Trailas en Apple Acres 10:30am-11:30am.
2. Parque de Chelan Falls 10:30am-11:30am.
3. Primaria Morgen Owings 10:30am-12:30pm.
4. Secundaria/Preparatoria de Chelan 10:30am-12:30pm.

post_text:
Lake Chelan School District athletics are following the expectations handed down by Gov. Inslee to all Washington Schools in relation to COVID-19.
Starting March 17th, all spring sports have been suspended until at least April 24th. This includes all events, all practices, and any organized activities at our school facilities. Coaches encourage students to stay active individually, but will not organize or supervise any practices until further notice.

post_text: Chelan Project Club members took an overnight cross country ski trip to one of the back country huts near Winthrop. The kids skied in approximately 7 miles, stayed overnight in the hut, and skied out the next day. They were rewarded with absolutely stunning star scapes and mountain views! The girls’ trip goes out in January. #chelanproject #crosscountryski #chelanschools #optoutside @ Winthrop, Washington

post_text:
Congratulations to our High School students who competed at state for Apple Evaluation this week!

The team of (pictured left to right) Molly Oswald, Macaela LaPorte, Aliyah Finch, Obed Diaz, and Clayton Reeves took 6th overall out of 25 teams in a very competitive field!

Macaela was 4th overall individual where the top 7 were all less than 10 points apart. Molly was 15th overall individual.

These students have put in a ton of time and effort for this achievement. Lunches, advisory, after school, and even coming in on weekends.

Special thanks to Jeff LaPorte for his time, support, and expertise. This team has had the amazing opportunity to work closely with him, and we wouldn’t have been as successful without him.

#appleevaluation #chelanschools #congratulations

post_text: The 2019 1A State Volleyball Champion Chelan Goats will be having a victory parade through downtown on Monday Nov. 18th starting at 3:30 pm followed by a community celebration at the Lake Chelan School District office (309 E. Johnson Ave). The team and staff will leave Chelan High School at 3:30 pm, be escorted over the old bridge, through downtown, and then to the the Lake Chelan School Distirct Office. We would like to invite all community members, families, students and fans to come and celebrate with a State Championship Social in the professional learning center of the district office. The social will go from 3:45 pm-5:00 pm.

post_text:
Although I am disappointed that the Bond was not successful, I want everyone to know that the Board of Directors and I remain undeterred in our vision and our efforts to better meet the needs of our students, staff and families.
While we are appreciative that community has always been supportive of our schools, the voter turnout was impressive and the message is clear. Therefore, the Board and I are committed to further study and finding creative solutions which the voters can endorse in the future.
-Barry DePaoli, Superintendent

post_text: Congratulations to Olivia Strandberg, who won the Regional Spelling Bee, and will be representing Chelan at the Scripps National Spelling Bee!
shared_text:
Chelan Middle School
March 19, 2019 at 9:32 PM ·

Chelan Middle School is so excited and proud to announce that Olivia Strandberg is the Regional Spelling Bee champion! After 9 rounds, the field was down to two spellers. Olivia correctly spelled “glockenspiel,” and after her opponent from Omak misspelled a tricky word (mnemonic), Olivia correctly spelled “lahar” for the win!

But Olivia’s not only the Regional Spelling Bee Champion... she has also won an all-expenses paid trip to Washington, DC to compete in the Scripps National Spelling Bee May 26-31! The spelling bee will be televised on ESPN. What an outstanding accomplishment!

Lauren Ware competed as well, and made it to the top 7 spellers! She was eliminated on the word “Kudzu”.

Go Lauren and go Olivia and go Pirates!!
